{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enumerated"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/EnumeratedSequence","text":"EnumeratedSequence"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"return-value","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Return Value"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A sequence of pairs enumerating the sequence."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example enumerates the characters of the string “Swift” and prints"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"each character along with its place in the string."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["for (n, c) in \"Swift\".enumerated() {","    print(\"\\(n): '\\(c)'\")","}","// Prints \"0: 'S'\"","// Prints \"1: 'w'\"","// Prints \"2: 'i'\"","// Prints \"3: 'f'\"","// Prints \"4: 't'\""]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you enumerate a collection, the integer part of each pair is a counter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the enumeration, but is not necessarily the index of the paired value."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These counters can be used as indices only in instances of zero-based,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"integer-indexed collections, such as "},{"code":"Array","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"ContiguousArray","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other collections the counters may be out of range or of the wrong type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to use as an index. To iterate over the elements of a collection with its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"indices, use the "},{"code":"zip(_:_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example iterates over the indices and elements of a set, building a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"list consisting of indices of names with five or fewer letters."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let names: Set = [\"Sofia\", \"Camilla\", \"Martina\", \"Mateo\", \"Nicolás\"]","var shorterIndices: [Set<String>.Index] = []","for (i, name) in zip(names.indices, names) {","    if name.count <= 5 {","        shorterIndices.append(i)","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that the "},{"code":"shorterIndices","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" array holds the indices of the shorter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"names in the "},{"code":"names","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" set, you can use those indices to access elements in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the set."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["for i in shorterIndices {","    print(names[i])","}","// Prints \"Sofia\"","// Prints \"Mateo\""]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"O(1)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Complexity"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/swift/string/utf8view/enumerated()"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/UTF8View"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns a sequence of pairs ("},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"), where "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consecutive integer starting at zero and "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"x"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" represents an element of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the sequence."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"enumerated"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"EnumeratedSequence","preciseIdentifier":"s:s18EnumeratedSequenceV"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"extendedModule":"Swift","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"enumerated()","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"externalID":"s:STsE10enumerateds18EnumeratedSequenceVyxGyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:SS8UTF8ViewV","symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/UTF8View/enumerated()"},"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String":{"url":"/documentation/swift/string","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"String","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"String","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"String","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Unicode string value that is a collection of characters."}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/EnumeratedSequence":{"url":"/documentation/swift/enumeratedsequence","title":"EnumeratedSequence","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier",